<div id="review_2434792424" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2434792424" />
    <a title="Sandra" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/8897687-sandra"><img alt="Sandra" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1623911574p2/8897687.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2434792424?book_show_action=true">Nov 06, 2018</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Sandra" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Sandra" href="/user/show/8897687-sandra">Sandra</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was ok"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was ok</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Kindle Edition " href="/book/show/38718956-manuscript-for-murder">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/8897687-sandra?shelf=mystery-suspense">mystery-suspense</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2434792424" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer4481197351382862669"><strong>Does not ring true</strong><br/><br/>Jessica would never say damn, and is not Mort&apos;s age. The snippy banter is out of character for Mort and her, who share a warm respectful relationship of trust. Lacks the true essence of Jessica. Too hard boiled, lacking Jessica&apos;s endearing thoughtful personality by substituting snippy banter. The body count and book within a book grew tiresome quickly. Disappointing.<br/>Skip to my review of MSW: Murder of Twelve #51 where the author is spot-on fantastic and entirely reinvigorates t</span>
  <span id="freeText4481197351382862669" style="display:none"><strong>Does not ring true</strong><br /><br />Jessica would never say damn, and is not Mort's age. The snippy banter is out of character for Mort and her, who share a warm respectful relationship of trust. Lacks the true essence of Jessica. Too hard boiled, lacking Jessica's endearing thoughtful personality by substituting snippy banter. The body count and book within a book grew tiresome quickly. Disappointing.<br />Skip to my review of MSW: Murder of Twelve #51 where the author is spot-on fantastic and entirely reinvigorates the series to keep you guessing!</span>
