  <div class="friendReviews elementListBrown" >
    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_2608075314" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2608075314" />
    <a title="Jeanie" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/15678788-jeanie"><img alt="Jeanie" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1576626924p2/15678788.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2608075314?book_show_action=true">Nov 27, 2018</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Jeanie" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Jeanie" href="/user/show/15678788-jeanie">Jeanie</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/15678788-jeanie?shelf=obs">obs</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2608075314" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer241998495401842642">While I am almost a newbie to this delightful, intelligent series, this is by far my favorite of the ones I&apos;ve read so far. Descriptions of the places Jessica goes are exciting and the characters are vibrant and realistic. The mystery is uniquely intriguing, and kept my attention throughout.<br/><br/>One by one, people are beginning to die around Jessica while in the Big Apple for a book-signing. The first person, an author who has hit hard times, is thought to have committed suicide or best case, a very </span>
  <span id="freeText241998495401842642" style="display:none">While I am almost a newbie to this delightful, intelligent series, this is by far my favorite of the ones I've read so far. Descriptions of the places Jessica goes are exciting and the characters are vibrant and realistic. The mystery is uniquely intriguing, and kept my attention throughout.<br /><br />One by one, people are beginning to die around Jessica while in the Big Apple for a book-signing. The first person, an author who has hit hard times, is thought to have committed suicide or best case, a very bad accident. When Jessica meets with their mutual publisher and long-time friend, she includes questions regarding irregularities in royalty payments alleged by the deceased author. The publisher declares innocence, and unwittingly gives Jessica a tiny clue. He also gives her a huge manuscript by a new author and asks her opinion on it. That night, the publisher died. Again, the police think it is a suicide. Jessica finally is able to have her long time friend on the NYPD to concede there might be a connection and does some investigating.<br /><br />The potential explosive novel is named The Affair and involves a president and his daughter who runs away from the White House after learning that her life was at risk. She had heard something that she wasn't supposed to, and her death is the only solution to keep the secrets. The plot is one that keeps Jessica turning pages, at least when death threats - or attempts! - are made on her life.<br /><br />Jessica and her Cabot Cove friends are as capable and well-depicted as ever, and it is a relief to know that Mort, Seth, and Artie, an NYPD lieutenant, have her back. Artie talks as if she is an annoyance to him, but I don't believe it for a second - he follows up on her concerns, especially after a murder attempt. When she tells Artie and Mort what she thinks is the central point of the murders, they don't want to accept it, until an attempt on her life occurs.<br /><br />There are plot twists and turns, and absolute surprises that I didn't see coming. It is an intricate, challenging mystery that I very much enjoyed trying to follow and solve. This armchair sleuth was stumped, however, coming up with only one facet of the whole. I finally settled in and watched Jessica's mind at work as she courageously went forward in spite of the dangers. I highly recommend this latest Murder She Wrote; it is delightful, intriguing, and frightening with a satisfying resolution.<br /><br />From a grateful heart: I received a copy of this book from the publisher, and this is my honest review.<br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="241998495401842642" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

